Hello Kiva! 

Thank you for your interest in my Kiva campaign. Also, checkout my campaign video link below to see exactly what I do and how your investment in my business will translate into growth and ultimately repayment of my Kiva loan I also encourage you to reach out to learn more.

Allow me to introduce myself, I’m Jacob P. Turner, 28 years old, originally from from the suburbs outside of Chicago and I currently live in Los Angeles, California. Growing up in the mid west taught me the value of passionate work and diligence in all things. I attended The University of Wisconsin where I studied music and architecture. In an effort to fully explore my passions and build a future for myself and my family, I moved to Los Angeles, California in 2013 and have been making my dreams a reality. 

Today, I manage a small portfolio of real estate investments primarily through the Airbnb platform. Airbnb is a popular online service offering unique short term rentals to millions of travelers worldwide. Airbnb’s home-sharing community is today’s answer to the popular vacation-rental by owner. Millions of unique properties with local flair is redefining hospitality and tourism like never before. 

My experience into the world of Airbnb started with one apartment. An immediate success, I began to host wonderful people from around the world and realized I had found something incredible. A business that allowed me to earn steady income while doing something I loved. I manage the entire operation from online communications, housekeeping and guest interactions. At this time I have 3 successful listings (please see the links below) and am looking to expand my hospitality business.

In addition to managing these listings I’m also involved in making music for television and film and in my spare time I drive for ride-sharing providers Uber, Lyft, Wings, and Instacart. It’s a sharing economy in Los Angeles and I am looking to expand with an additional Airbnb property. Each property requires some capital to get started and that’s why I’m reaching out to Kiva and it’s community of investors.

With your help I plan to expand on my already successful Airbnb business with the addition of a new property. Specifically, I will use this Kiva loan to cover upfront costs including deposit, setup costs and operating capital. 

With your help I will be able to take my business to the next level and build a solid future for myself and my family. Please reach out if you have additional questions and I thank you in advance for supporting my Kiva Campaign.

Sincerely,
Jacob P. Turner

I was born and raised in Louisville, KY, raised in the Chickasaw and Historic Parkland Neighborhood. I can remember as a young girl taking walks with my grandfather to the Parkland area department stores, banks and nice restaurant’s.  As a young child my Grandfather taught me about supporting local businesses and helping your community. Those were the good old days, and the lessons taught on those walks will always be a part of me. 

Now My grandmother Mattie taught me something special as well, and that’s the gift of cooking and sharing great food! At the age of nine, I begin assisting and working under her, learning and remembering every recipe and technique by memory. My grandmother not only taught me the secrets to a great meal, she also taught me how to have good character and be a person who knows how to care for others. Not only did my Grandma cook for her family, but she fed those in the community who was in need as well. My Grandmother passed in 1980, and I promised her, I would keep cooking and sharing the love through her recipes.

In 1992, I attended Kentucky Technical College, where I received my certificate and license as a Certified Nursing Assistant. I worked here in Louisville for the Visiting Nurse Association for ten years caring for others. I didn’t want to give up on my promise and dream to one day open a catering business dedicated to my late grandmother. I left the Visiting Nurse Association, and became and in home care caregiver, and a fulltime preschool teacher for the YMCA. I am now retired and am ready to take on cooking and catering full time.
